<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-101] Attribute &quot;format&quot; for SyslogAppender is mandatory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-101</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the SyslogAppender the configuration attribute &quot;Format&quot; must be present, otherwise a NullPointerException is thrown in method &quot;createAppender&quot; when the following statement is executed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (format.equalsIgnoreCase(RFC5424))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is simply to add a check so the &quot;equalsIgnoreCase&quot; is called only if the format variable isn&apos;t Null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
